Preheat your oven to 220°C. Lay the @British chicken thighs{4} on a lined #baking tray{}. Sprinkle over the @dried oregano{3/4%tsp} and season with @salt{}. Drizzle on a glug of @oil{} and rub the seasoning into the chicken. Halve the @lemon{1/2}. Set one half aside and slice the other into thin half moons. Pop one on each thigh. Roast on the top shelf of your oven, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Pop your #kettle{} on to boil. Chop the @salad potatoes{350%g} in half (no need to peel) or quarters if they are large, and pop in a large #saucepan{}. Cover with boiling water and add a good pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cook over medium-high heat, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> TIP: The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through. When done, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan to keep warm.

Meanwhile, trim the tops from the @green beans{200%g}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Finely chop the @chives{1/2%bunch} (or use #scissors{} if it's easier).

Heat a splash of @oil{for frying} in a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the shallot to the pan and cook until soft stirring occasionally, ~{3%minutes}. Add the green beans and a splash of @water{}. Cover the pan with a #lid{} (or some #foil{}) and steam until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Transfer to a #bowl{} and cover with foil to keep warm. Wipe the pan out as we will need it for the sauce.

Put the now empty frying pan on high heat. Pour in @water{100%ml} and stir in the @chicken stock powder{1/2%tsp}. Bring to the boil. Stir to dissolve the stock powder, then lower the heat to medium. Stir (or whisk) in the @unsalted butter{30%g} and then remove from the heat. Stir in half the chives and add a squeeze of lemon juice. Set aside and get ready to serve.

Season the potatoes with @pepper{}. Add a drizzle of @oil{for dressing} and sprinkle over the remaining chives. Share the potatoes between your #plates{}. Lay the chicken and green beans alongside. Spoon over the buttery sauce. Enjoy!